    <item>
      <title>Good Bye PHP5 😥</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/php5-end/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 03 Jan 2019 20:07:37 +0100</pubDate><author>rajekevin@hotmail.fr (Rajekevin)</author>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/php5-end/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 class=&#34;title&#34;&gt;Good Bye PHP5 [14.04.2004-31.12.2018] &lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;14 years of love story with PHP5, now finish, since the new year 2019 !
&lt;img src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/img/posts/post2/php5.PNG&#34; height=&#34;350px&#34; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I started, learned, praticed with this version of PHP.
Now PHP5, since December 31, 2018, security support for PHP 5.6.x is officially cease ; marking the end of all support for any version of the ancient PHP 5.x branch 😥&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 class=&#34;title&#34; &gt; What does it mean ?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It exposes hundreds of millions of websites (who still running on PHP 5.x version), to serious security risks ☠️.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Render Html Tags</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/render-html-tags/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 02 Jan 2019 19:45:06 +0100</pubDate><author>rajekevin@hotmail.fr (Rajekevin)</author>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/render-html-tags/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 class=&#34;title&#34;&gt; Render HTML Tags &lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When you store HTML tags in your database, you would like to retrieve these datas as HTML Content, not  a string right ?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;
&lt;table class=&#34;lntable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-PHP&#34; data-lang=&#34;PHP&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nx&#34;&gt;php&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;k&#34;&gt;echo&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;nv&#34;&gt;$row&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;s1&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;description&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;];&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;cp&#34;&gt;?&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;err&#34;&gt;`
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Maybe when you want to display this data, it show  as a string character  : &lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;
&lt;table class=&#34;lntable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-HTML&#34; data-lang=&#34;HTML&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nt&#34;&gt;ul&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nt&#34;&gt;li&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;Hello, I am PHP&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nt&#34;&gt;li&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nt&#34;&gt;ul&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Don&amp;rsquo;t worry, call your best elePHPhant 🐘 and use &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.php.net/manual/fr/function.htmlspecialchars-decode.php&#34;&gt;htmlspecialchars_decode()&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The htmlspecialchars() function converts some predefined characters to HTML entities&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
